  "intent_precise": "Mass Spec Sample Prep: Using mag_plate (plate, slot 2), reagent plate (plate, slot 5), ethanol plate (plate, slot 2), acetonitrile plate (plate, slot 3). With magnetic module, thermocycler module, temperature module. (1) Pause for manual intervention. (2) Transfer 5\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (3) Incubate for 30 minutes. (4) Transfer 5\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (5) Incubate for 30 minutes. (6) Transfer 15\u00b5L from source (A1, A1) to destination (A1, A1). (7) Pause: Please move plate from thermocycler to magnetic module. Resume when the plate has been moved. (8) Engage magnets for bead separation. (9) Incubate for 5 minutes. (10) Transfer 43\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (11) Disengage magnets to release beads. (12) Transfer 200\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (13) Engage magnets for bead separation. (14) Incubate for 5 minutes. (15) Transfer 230\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (16) Pause: Please replace the ethanol plate (slot 6) with a fresh plate of ethanol before resuming. (17) Disengage magnets to release beads. (18) Transfer 172\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (19) Engage magnets for bead separation. (20) Incubate for 5 minutes. (21) Transfer 230\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (22) Pause: Place plate in thermocycler (23) Distribute 5\u00b5L from source A1 to destination wells A1-A1 (4 wells).",
  "intent_concise": "Perform distribute to A1-A1 (4 wells), magnetic bead separation. (volumes 5\u00b5L-230\u00b5L, ~76 min total)",
  "intent": "For this mass spec sample prep, you'll be working with the mag plate in slot 2, reagent plate in slot 5, ethanol plate in slot 2, and acetonitrile plate in slot 3, using the magnetic, thermocycler, and temperature modules. Start by pausing for any manual setup, then do two rounds of 5\u00b5L transfers from A1 to A1 with 30-minute incubations between each, followed by a 15\u00b5L transfer. You'll need to manually move the plate from the thermocycler to the magnetic module, then engage magnets for 5 minutes before transferring 43\u00b5L, adding 200\u00b5L wash, incubating 5 minutes, and removing 230\u00b5L - remember to replace the ethanol plate in slot 6 with fresh ethanol before the second wash cycle. Finish by transferring 172\u00b5L, doing a final magnetic separation with 5-minute incubation and 230\u00b5L removal, then place the plate back in the thermocycler and distribute 5\u00b5L from A1 across wells A1-A1 (4 wells total).",
